  <ability>
    <abilitytitle>Shatter</abilitytitle>
    <abilityid>shatter</abilityid>    
    <abilityranks from="1" to="3"/>
    <abilitycheck>
      <defaults>elemental_defaults</defaults>
      <defaults>pool_cost_2</defaults>
      <actiontype><standard/></actiontype>
      <critsuccess></critsuccess>
      <critfail></critfail>
      <!-- <boon></boon> -->
      <!-- <bane></bane> -->
      <range><na/></range>
      <!-- <keywords><magicpool/></keywords> -->
      <!-- <indifferent>1</indifferent> -->
      <!-- <dc>11</dc> -->
    </abilitycheck>
    <prereqabilityrank>elemental_magic_2</prereqabilityrank>
    <spline><p x="60" y="60"/></spline>
    <abilitydescription>
      <p>
	When casting shatter the caster intones magical words
	and strikes a target of stone, metal or ice (in fact anything
	elemental in nature, including wood).
      </p>

      <p>
	This spell is particularly effective for bringing down small structures
	supported by columns or arches, or for breaching doors.  However city
	walls and towers are designed to take a lot of damage without failing
	and are effectively immune from the effects of this spell.
      </p>

      <p>
	This spell may also be used to attack a subset of monsters, including
	earth and water elementals, metalic, stone or earthen constructs, and
	natural wooden animates.  For most other creatures this spell does no
	damage. Against these monsters roll to hit with a grounding weapon
	(staff or spear) and the spell does Weapon damage plus an additional
	10+7xRank damage.
      </p>
    </abilitydescription>    
  </ability>

  
